In order to continue the momentum of the MDGs and the unfinished business, the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development was unanimously adopted by the world's 193 leaders at the United Nations Development Summit in 2015, establishing the SDGs. Therefore, in order to explicitly consider the time-series change characteristics of IEE when SDGs are considered, and taking into account data availability, this paper takes 2015–2021 as the research period. The research objects are 30 provinces, autonomous regions, and cities in China (excluding Hong Kong, Macao, Taiwan, and Tibet). According to the different stages included in the development of industrial ecology, and by referring to the research ideas of Shao et al. (2021), the following steps are taken to screen the relevant indicators of SDG6 and SDG7 for localization in China (Fig. 2
                           ) and to construct the evaluation indicator system from the levels of input and output systems (Table 2
                           ). The relevant data are obtained from the China Statistical Yearbook, China Energy Statistical Yearbook, China Industrial Economic Statistical Yearbook, China Electric Power Yearbook, China Environmental Statistical Yearbook, National Environmental Statistical Bulletin, China Water Resources Statistical Yearbook, and China Regional Economic Statistical Yearbook in the past years. Table 2 shows the descriptive statistical information of the sample, which to some extent reflects the imbalance of development between regions.
